details: Thank you for your inquiry regarding the traffic signal at MacArthur Boulevard and Norton Street%2fLoughboro Road. You indicated that the signal only turns green for Norton Street if a vehicle is present and does not turn green otherwise. We have reviewed the operation and confirmed that this is the correct and intended operation of the signal. This was recently implemented in order to implement safety improvements at the intersection%2c namely the elimination of the vehicular and pedestrian conflict caused by the heavy dual westbound left turn from Loughboro Road onto southbound MacArthur Boulevard. Norton Street will only receive a green indication when vehicles are present and will otherwise remain red.  We will continue to monitor this intersection for safe multi-modal traffic operation.%0aAnthony Dinkins%2c 202-671-4634%2c Transportation Engineer. %0a%0a

details: Study Completed -Traffic Calming.%0aBased on the study findings summarized the roadway classification%2c traffic conditions on the 100 block of 33rd Street%2c NE do not warrant traffic calming measures at this time. %0aIn general%2c a traffic calming assessment evaluates the roadway to determine if the physical environment facilitates speeding. DDOT looks at the speeds at which most drivers travel to determine the speeds that the physical environment allows. The 85th percentile speed is used extensively in the field of traffic engineering and safety to characterize the speeds at which reasonable and prudent drivers travel given the geometric and operational constraints of the roadway. DDOT%e2%80%99s eligibility criteria require that the 85th percentile speed of vehicles (measured over a 48-hour period) must exceed the posted speed limit by at least 25 percent in order to qualify for traffic calming measures. In other words%2c at least 15 percent of drivers must exceed the speed limit by a minimum of 25 percent for traffic calming measures to be considered which would enable physical changes to be made to the roadway. In this case%2c the measured 85th percentile speed is 21 MPH%3b therefore%2c DDOT will not make physical changes to the block.%0a
